 scenarios.\\n    65→\\n    66→### Phase 3: Implement\\n    67→\\n    68→Build the Go agent package using E2E-driven development. Reads internal Entire docs (agent-guide, checklist, interfaces) and uses the one-pager for all agent-specific details (hook format, transcript location, config structure).\\n    69→\\n    70→Read and follow the implement procedure from `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`.\\n    71→\\n    72→**Expected output:** Complete agent package at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/` with all tests passing.\\n    73→\\n    74→**Note:** `AGENT.md` is a living document — Phases 2 and 3 update it when they discover new information during testing or implementation.\\n    75→\\n    76→## Final Validation\\n    77→\\n    78→After all three phases, run the complete validation:\\n    79→\\n    80→```bash\\n    81→mise run fmt      # Format\\n    82→mise run lint     # Lint\\n    83→mise run test:ci  # All tests (unit + integration)\\n    84→```\\n    85→\\n    86→Summarize:\\n    87→- Compatibility verdict from Phase 1\\n    88→- Files created in Phases 2 and 3\\n    89→- Test coverage\\n    90→- Any remaining TODOs or gaps\\n    91→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"e9e01de0-6e86-4344-94b3-269ba65291b3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T18:39:33.146Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot/.claude/skills/agent-integration/SKILL.md\",\"content\":\"---\\nname: agent-integration\\ndescription: >\\n  Run all three agent integration phases sequentially: research, write-tests,\\n  and implement. For individual phases, use /agent-integration:research,\\n  /agent-integration:write-tests, or /agent-integration:implement.\\n  Use when the user says \\\"integrate agent\\\", \\\"add agent support\\\", or wants\\n  to run the full agent integration pipeline end-to-end.\\n---\\n\\n# Agent Integration — Full Pipeline\\n\\nRun all three phases of agent integration in a single session. Parameters are collected once and